{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ぬじ}}

{{IPAfont|⟨nuzi⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/nuʑi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=ぬじ|-}}<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>, attested in the {{m|ja||北野本日本書紀|tr=Kitano-bon {{w|Nihon shoki}}}} of the late {{w|Heian period}}.<ref name="kotobank">{{cite-web|work=虹・霓(にじ)とは - コトバンク|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E8%99%B9-109343|accessdate=2019-01-21}}</ref>  May be a shift from earlier ''noji'' (see below); compare {{cog|ryu|ぬーじ|tr=nuː‎dʑi}} and {{cog|mvi|ぬず|tr=nudzɿ}}.

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|のじ}}

{{IPAfont|⟨no<sub>1</sub>zi⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/noʑi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=のじ|-}}, appeared in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' of 759 {{CE}} as an eastern dialectal variant.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="kotobank" /><ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|14|3414}}, text available [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man14Yo.html#3414 here]</ref>

Cognate with {{cog|ryu|ぬーじ|tr=nuː‎dʑi}} and {{cog|mvi|ぬず|tr=nudzɿ}}.
